Jenkins-

sudo -i

yum provides java

Then, Choose any Java version above 17 and install it.

yum install  java-17-amazon-corretto-1:17.0.10+7-1.amzn2023.1.x86_64 -y

Now, 

we need install Jenkins

Go to this , https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/#red-hat-centos
 
 and run the command one by one.
 
wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
    https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
  
 
 
rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key


yum upgrade

yum install jenkins

 systemctl start jenkins
 systemctl enable jenkins
 
 Done...
 
 